T SIZE=-2>HE TRANSMISSIBLE SPONGIFORM ENCEPHALOPATHIES are fatal neurodegenerative diseases caused by prions. They include Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease, Gertsmann-Straussler-Scheinker syndrome, kuru, and fatal familial insomnia in humans, scrapie in sheep and goats, and bovine spongiform encephalopathy in cattle. Prion diseases are believed to result from the conformational change of the PrPc to PrPsc
